      <prompt>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 16-year-old boy presents to his GP with a history of renal stones. He is found to have the following biochemical test results:</p>
              <p>Corrected calcium 2.91 mmol/L (normal range 2.1–2.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Phosphate 0.65 mmol/L (normal range 0.8–1.4 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Parathyroid hormone level 6 pmol/L (normal range 1.0–6.5 pmol/L)</p>
              <p>His family also has a history of renal stones.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 64-year-old man presents with gradual onset bone pain. He complains of hearing loss and finds that his hats no longer fit him. He has the following biochemical test results:</p>
              <p>Corrected calcium 2.51 mmol/L (normal range 2.1–2.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Phosphate 1.06 mmol/L (normal range 0.8–1.4 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Parathyroid hormone level 4 pmol/L (normal range 1.0–6.5 pmol/L)</p>
              <p>Alkaline phosphatase 150 (normal range 40–125 iu/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 64-year-old woman presents with abdominal pains, fatigue and muscle weakness. She has the following biochemical test results:</p>
              <p>Corrected calcium 2.70 mmol/L (normal range 2.1–2.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Phosphate 0.61 mmol/L (normal range 0.8–1.4 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Parathyroid hormone level 7 pmol/L (normal range 1.0–6.5 pmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 45-year-old man presents with insidious onset of bone pains, backaches and muscle weakness. He has a previous history of coeliac disease.</p>
              <p>He has the following biochemical test results:</p>
              <p>Corrected calcium 2.10 mmol/L (normal range 2.1–2.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Phosphate 0.64 mmol/L (normal range 0.8–1.4 mmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </prompt>
