  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option A (Familial hypocalciuric hypercalcaemia) is Correct.</b>
      Familial hypocalciuric hypercalcaemia (FHH) often presents asymptomatically apart from incidental finding of hypercalcaemia and inappropriate normal/raised PTH levels. FHH is associated with loss of function of the calcium-sensing receptor (CaSR) gene.
    </p>
  </modalFeedback>
